{% import "./m_teaser.pattern" as pattern %}
{% import "../m_patternBlock/m_patternBlock.pattern" as block %}
{% set d %}
{% markdown %}
`m_teaser` renders a teaser article block. It accepts a `posts` object and optional `hLevel` and `classes` strings. Its designed to give a lead-in to an article.
{% endmarkdown %}
{% endset %}
{{ block.m_patternBlock(d,'pattern.m_teaser(posts)') }}
<div class="m_patternBlock m_patternBlock--eg">
    {{pattern.m_teaser(posts=eg_article)}}
</div>
